casebody.data:
Malcolm Claude BAUGH, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 11367. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit Dec. 18, 1945. Edgar W. Waybright, Sr., of Jacksonville, Fla., for appellant. H. S. Phillips, U. S. Atty., and D. New-comb Barco, Jr., Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Tampa, Fla., for appellee.

Before HOLMES, McCORD, and LEE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment appealed from in this case is affirmed upon the authority of Biron v. Collins, 5 Cir., 145 F.2d 758.
